Text.Value: You there! A friendly face. You haven't the looks of one of these cultists about you, no sir!

EditorData.logicalname: In cage, not met in camp

Text.Value: I guarantee the story of your daring rescue of my person will live on for aeons!
What career could possibly involve getting locked up by goblins?
Once I've written you into one of my books, there won't be a tavern in Faer√ªn you can enter without receiving a hero's welcome.
Bless you, my friend! I'll wait nicely, but please don't tarry!
I'm not looking for extra company right now. You go your way, I go mine.
We met in the druids' grove, don't you remember?
Slip the yoke? How do you intend to do that exactly?
Smashing! Soon, my friend - soon we can share a flagon of something liquid and a tale of derring-do!
Gods bless you, friend. I'll wait 'til the coast is quite clear and be gone!

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Volo has been freed and is waiting for player to leave the region so he can disappear out of sight.
EditorData.logicalname: Volo is freed. waits for moment.

Text.Value: Ah! My friend! We can speak freely.

EditorData.logicalname: In cage, has met in camp

Text.Value: You're Volo, right? I've read your work.
Ha-HA! I knew I could count on you, my friend.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Player] opens the cage door. [Volo] exits the cage, nearly pushing the player out of the way - Matt
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The cage is unlocked. Player talked to Volo prior to unlocking the cage.
EditorData.SFXTags: Sound of the cage door opening

Text.Value: Aha! An individual of some learning, I see. You're quite right.
Ha-HA! Hang the key - I see you've no need at all! Thank you for your help, my friend.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Player got Volo out of the cage (teleport i.e.) and talked to him prior to releasing.

Text.Value: I intend to do just that. A trusty invisibility potion goes a long way in a place like this.
But! No matter. Here I am and here you are. Please - unlock this cell and we can both of us escape.
Pish posh! Allies are a difficult find in the area, my friend. You'll want Volo in your corner, believe you me.
I'll write an anonymous account of your heroism, then! None will know your name, yet your doings will live on!
Ah, of course. Good thing we cleared out of there, by the by. These goblins are planning a raid on the place as we speak.
I'm not looking for that sort of attention.
You know what else lives on for aeons? Gold. You owe me.
Get yourself to safety - and quick.
I'm not interested in that sort of attention.
Bah, what's a bit of metal between allies? I'll do one better.
Volothamp Geddarm, realm-renowned author, auteur, and tastemaker, at your service.
All right - I'll get you out.
A joy to see a familiar face in such a... precarious setting.
Tell me where we can meet each other, once we've slipped the goblin yoke, and I'll offer much more than gold. Knowledge, my friend, is priceless.
This lock, my friend! Surely a strong arm like you can make short work of it.

EditorData.logicalname: In cage, has met in cage

Text.Value: A fine mess you landed yourself in. How'd you get caught?
I don't need a promise, my friend. Only an honest attempt. Please - do consider it!
I'm in no hurry to take my turn on that spit out front. Perhaps you'd be so kind as to unlock this cage?
And you expect me to help you in return for nothing?
Well, I suppose this is 'goodbye,' my friend. I wish you the greatest of luck and I hope I shall recall you favourably in my records of the day's events.
Remember my name when you're crediting the story's author. It's [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53].
Help me, and I'll make sure everyone in Faer√ªn knows you for the hero you are.
Open this cell and I'll never forget the kindness!
We mustn't tarry, but I'd hate for our friendship to end here. Please - won't you meet me, once we've both slipped the goblin yoke?
Don't you remember me?
I'll think about it. No promises.
Why... of course! You were the one with the... name!
Leave.
I'll slip away when the coast is clear. See you soon, my friend! I simply can't wait to pick your brain!
You may not recognise me in these dire straits, but my name is Volothamp Geddarm, realm-renowned author, auteur, and tastemaker.
Of course not! As compensation, I can assure the tale of your heroism will live on... forever!
I'll slip away when the coast is clear. And I wish you the greatest possible luck in your mysterious endeavours. Ta!
Volothamp Geddarm, realm-renowned author, auteur, and tastemaker, at your service.
An invisibility potion, my friend. A bit less refined than your mendacious methods, but by god it'll do the trick!
I'll write an anonymous account of your largesse, then! None will know your name, yet your doings will live on!
We mustn't tarry, but I'd hate for our friendship to end here. Please - won't you meet me, once we've both slipped the goblin yoke?
Curiosity, my friend. It didn't benefit the cat, but it's the foundation of my career.
Please - a hand?
Volothamp Geddarm, realm-renowned author, auteur, and tastemaker, at your service.
How did you end up in this place?
Leave.
And just how do you propose doing that?
Why, by design, my friend. How better to learn the ways of a people than to live among them?
That's all? Hardly seems worth the trouble.
I daresay the experiment has proven most fruitful, too. I'll be happy to share my findings... once we've found somewhere safe to parley.
Go to my camp. We'll talk there, once we're both safe.
Volothamp Geddarm, realm-renowned author, auteur, and tastemaker, at your service.
Volothamp Geddarm, realm-renowned author, auteur, and tastemaker, at your service.
Though I admit I've hit something of an impasse. Please - unlock my cell?
That will sound ridiculous. But, fine. If you insist. As much as it pains me to cede creative control...
Ha-HA! Look at this - I'm quite saved, and by means most extraordinary!

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Player got Volo out of the cage (teleport i.e.) and DIDN'T talked to him prior to releasing.

Text.Value: Well, I will be at your service. Once I've been freed from this ensconsement. Speaking of which...
Ha-HA! Look at this - I'm quite saved!

Text.Value: Then please, a favour - notable figure to notable figure.
And just how will you be accomplishing that?

Synopsis: Volo has been caught by the goblins and imprisoned. He has an invisbility potion he can use to escape once he's out of the cage, but he needs the player's help. He's a combination of desperate for help and his usal, confident self.
